<p>This applies to Border Patrol, too?  </p>
<p>I&#8217;ve seen video showing that BP has vehicle checkpoints 40-plus miles north of the US&#8217;s southern border.  The question that they ask is:  &#8220;Are you an American citizen?&#8221;  Should one answer (specifically, if one <i>is</i> an American citizen) this question?  It seems wrong to me that government agents are asking this question, not at the border, but many miles away from it, within the United States &#8212; for this area, so far away from the border, doesn&#8217;t seem to be within BP&#8217;s jurisdiction, no?  But, if you are a citizen, and you answer their question, &#8220;That is none of your business,&#8221; you will be harrassed and/or threatened with a search of your vehicle, and possibly imrisoned.  </p>
<p>Please share your opinion.  Thank you.</p>
